I"%<p>In crude approximations, <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/brain-is-like-hardware-mind-is-like-software">the brain</a> is orders of magnitude more energy efficient than a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/digital-is-pejorative">digital computer</a> for the same level of compute. <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/digital-is-pejorative">Post-digital computing paradigms</a> based on other physical elements than transistors (e.g. photonic, quantum, neuromorphic) promise energy efficiency on par with the brain.</p>
